page.title: 20NATURAL HISTORY,KNEESALL
page.content:
{BIRD LIFE} The area is rich in bird life.Among single sightings of rare birds are;a{ {Hoopoe,}a{Wryneck,}a{Nutcracker,}a{ {Common Scoter}and a{Great Grey Shrike. Five species of{Owls}and three species of{Woodpecker}have been seen here.A{ {Nightingale}appeared in a village garden.A{Hen Harrier}has been seen too.Altogether 98 species have been recorded over 3 years.
